Protect yourself and your helper with these employment agreement guidelines Employment contracts are an important way of protecting the rights of both the employer and employee and are equally important for people you hire to help maintain your household “When agreeing to hire someone, it is important that there’s an agreement in writing. This is to protect both parties in the case of any disputes and contracts are there to serve this purpose, which can be highly beneficial to both parties,” says Tertius Bossert, Operations Manager at FNB Law on Call. READ MORE: Steps to take to be a better employer to your domestic worker These are the five non-negotiables that should be contained in a domestic worker’s contract: READ MORE: Kulani Mtileni on creating sustainable jobs for domestic workers